Abuse Exposed Components via Drozer
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure Drozer framework for Android security testing
Identify exposed Android components (Activities, Services, Broadcast Receivers, Content Providers)
Craft and deliver exploit payloads to vulnerable components
Automate component scanning using Python scripts
Document security findings and recommend mitigations
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Android application architecture and components
Familiarity with Linux command line and ADB commands
Python programming fundamentals
Understanding of mobile application security concepts
